<br>
I have no problem with this.  In fact, I think it is great!  I am an American, and the only language that I can speak fluently is English.  I have a strong interest in German and can usually follow a conversation, even if I do speak it badly after 5 years of classes.  I don't mind not being able to understand what people are saying to each other (notice each other, not me =) because I think it adds flavor to the game.  On CT, I would rarely come across Europeans speaking a native language.  I see it all the time now, and it serves to remind me that no only are all these characters indeed real people, but they are from all over the world.<br>
<br>
